# .gitignore — peership-corpus
#
# What belongs in this repository: the frozen PDFs, the editable sources that
# exist, the arXiv submission source, the apparatus, and the documentation.
# What does not: build by-products, archive bundles, duplicates, and anything
# private.
#
# NOTE ON GIT LFS: Git LFS is deliberately NOT used. The corpus PDFs are small
# enough for ordinary Git, and LFS would add a fetch dependency, a bandwidth
# quota, and a way for a clone to arrive without its papers. Plain Git objects
# are the more durable choice for an archival corpus.


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LaTeX build by-products
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.aux
*.log
*.out
*.toc
*.fls
*.fdb_latexmk
*.synctex.gz
*.blg
*.bcf
*.run.xml
*.nav
*.snm
*.vrb

# EXCEPTION: *.bbl is NOT ignored.
#
# The usual LaTeX .gitignore drops .bbl as a BibTeX by-product. Here it is a
# required deliverable: arXiv does not run BibTeX, so the compiled bibliography
# must be shipped inside the submission package. Losing it would silently break
# the arXiv build of the Thesis.
#
#   corpus/05-peership-thesis/arxiv/main.bbl  — REQUIRED, committed.
#
# The negations below are belt-and-braces: no pattern above matches .bbl today,
# and none may be added later that does.
!*.bbl
!corpus/05-peership-thesis/arxiv/main.bbl


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Archive bundles (Zenodo uploads, arXiv submissions)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The extracted arXiv SOURCE is committed — corpus/05-peership-thesis/arxiv/
# {main.tex, main.bbl, references.bib} — because source is what can be read,
# diffed, and corrected. The zips are not: they are re-derivable packaging, and
# the authoritative bundle already lives in the Zenodo record.
*.zip


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Duplicates, temporary copies, and render artifacts
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*(1).*
* (1).*
*~
*.bak
*render-check*
*draft-final*
*_draft[0-9]*

# DOS/8.3-truncated filenames produced by some PDF and mail tools
*~1.PDF
*~1.pdf
*~[0-9].PDF
*~[0-9].pdf


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Operating-system metadata
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
._*


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor and IDE settings
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Private material — never committed
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Credentials, tokens, and local environment files. See PROVENANCE.md §6: the
# non-disclosure of prompts, transcripts, and account data is deliberate.
*.env
.env*
*credentials*
*token*
*secret*
